@node Software


                               Bridgeboard Software

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------


				------
				
			@{"SXServ" link SXServ}	Commodity replacement for PCwindow/flipper/LPT
				------

 SXServ is a little commodity that combines some programs of the original
janus package such as PCReset,LPT1,LPT1X,Flipper and PCWindow.

All these functions are available via a single commodity and/or hotkeys.


* With a little circuit you can realize an electronic monitorswitch with the
  A2386 bridgeboard. The switch is plugged into the minidinconnector at the
  back of the commodore sx board.

Aminet: misc/emu/JanusTools.lha
				
				-------
				
			@{"AmiCDex" link AmiCDex}	Share Amiga CD-ROM with the PC
				-------

This software should be of interest to anyone who has an Amiga with a PC/AT
emulator board, and an installed Amiga CD-ROM drive.

AmiCDEx allows you to access your amiga CD-ROM Drive from your PC/AT Emulator 
board without letting the PC realize that this is infact an Amiga CD-ROM drive. 
All commands coming from PC is redirected to Amiga CD-ROM drive.
It also features user configurable cacheing by the amiga of data from the CD_ROM.

Limitations: play-audio capabilities under MS-DOS is not implementated in the
	     present version.


Aminet: misc/emu/AmiCDex.lha

				-------
				
			@{"DOSServ" link DOSServ}	Use Amiga partitions as PC hard disks.
				-------

Dosserv is a replacement to Commodore's DOSServ included in the Janus software
package  version  2.1.   It  will  give  you the possibility to use a physical
harddiscpartition directly.


Aminet: misc/emu/JanusTools.lha

				-------
				
			@{"PCDisk" link PCDisk}	Use Amiga partitions as PC hard disks.
				-------

PCDisk makes an entire hard disk partition appear as a single AmigaDOS file to 
programs, allowing Janus to use that partition to create a disk file for the 
Bridgeboard hard disk image. 

Since all file i/o can go directly to the partition without having to go through 
the standard AmigaDOS filesystem, performance is improved (particulary for writes). 

Also included is information on mounting such a partition as a crossdos filesystem.

Limitations:	If you are not comfortable with mountlists, partitions, etc. don't 
		try this it's not for the fainthearted!


Aminet: misc/emu/PCDisk91b.lha


				----------
				
			@{"JanusPatch" link Jpatch}	Use Amiga RAM as PC EMS memory
				----------

JanusPatch is required, if you use the bridgeboard in conjunction with a 040
system and a fast scsi dma controller. This patch has to be started in before
binddrivers is executed.


Aminet: misc/emu/JanusTools.lha

				--------
			@{"AmigaEMS" link AEMS}	Use Amiga RAM as PC EMS memory
				--------



AmigaEMS is a utility program for the Amiga bridgeboard.

AmigaEMS allows you to use Amiga RAM as expanded memory for 
the bridgeboard. AmigaEMS is LIM/EMS 4.0 compatible.

AmigaEMS supports non-volatile expanded memory. This means the
contents of expanded memory can survive a reset. This feature is
found on very expensive PC expanded memory cards only. 

Copying memory from the PC to the Amiga (vice versa) thru the janus
interface takes time. For this reason AmigaEMS isn't as fast as a
true EMS card. However, AmigaEMS is faster than an EMS driver with
a disk-based swapping area!

Limitations: The unregistered version can only handle 384k of EMS memory.

	     It will not work with PC programs that use expanded memory
	     and are started in the Config.Sys file as well. E.g. ramdrives
	     for the PC won't work. This is a limitation of the janus software.

Aminet: misc/emu/AmigaEMS.lha	(Main archive)
                /AMEMS152.lha   (C=2386 update)




